    @Override
    public void fax(String recipient) {
        System.out.println("Sending digital fax to " + recipient);
    }
}
```
In this refactored code, each class only implements the methods that it needs, and no class is forced to implement methods that it doesn't use. This makes the code more maintainable and less prone to errors.

