In this refactored code, each interface has a single responsibility. The Circle and Rectangle classes implement the IShape2D interface which only includes methods for calculating area and perimeter. The Line class implements the IShape1D interface with methods for calculating perimeter. Lastly, the Cube class implements both interfaces: IShape3D (which inherits from IShape2D) and includes a method for calculating volume.

